1. Introduction

This is a ABE218 project conductd during my undergraduate study at spring 2015.

Link to ISU College of Engineering News: New technology in ABE advances engineering design skills for students

The software in used include the following:

  • Excel: balance calculation
  • Adobe Illustrator: Vector drawing
  • SolidWorld: 3D model construction.

2. Balance Calculation

The step of this engineering design includes the following:

  1. Sketch or print of parts to cut;
  2. Estimated mass (weight) and CG for each part;
  3. Calculation showing that your predicted Angle of Installation is close to a zero error.
